cs.CR, cs.CY, cs.SI, cs.HC, cs.SE 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security): The paper discusses the ePrivacy Directive and its aim to regulate online tracking technologies, which falls under the domain of cybersecurity and privacy. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society): The paper also discusses the impact of the ePrivacy Directive on users and websites, which relates to the social and ethical implications of technology. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): The paper mentions the technical difficulties of webmasters in implementing the Directive, which could be related to network and system infrastructure. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction): The paper discusses the implementation of the Cookie Bar and its impact on user experience, which falls under the domain of HCI. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper mentions the lack of tools to verify the implementation of the Directive, which could be related to software testing and verification.
